### Core Concepts — DEEP DIVE

**Horn Clauses:**
- A clause with **at most one positive literal**
- Written as: A :- B1, B2, ..., Bn (Head :- Body)
- **Definite clause:** exactly one positive literal (a rule or fact)
- **Goal clause:** zero positive literals (a query)
- Horn Clauses when written as logical implication: head has at most one positive literal, body is conjunction of zero or more positive literals

> [!IMPORTANT]
