## WEEK 9: DESCRIPTION LOGIC (DL) & ALC

### Core Concepts — DEEP DIVE

**Description Logic (DL):**
- A family of logics for **knowledge representation**
- More expressive than propositional logic, less than FOL
- Has **decidable** reasoning (unlike FOL!)
- Used as the formal basis for **OWL** (Web Ontology Language)

**ALC = Attributive Language with Complement:**

| Constructor | Syntax | Semantics | Example |
|-------------|--------|-----------|---------|
| Top | ⊤ | Everything | The universal concept |
| Bottom | ⊥ | Nothing | The empty concept |
| Conjunction | C ⊓ D | Intersection | Student ⊓ Athlete |
| Disjunction | C ⊔ D | Union | Doctor ⊔ Lawyer |
| Negation | ¬C | Complement | ¬Student |
| Existential | ∃R.C | At least one R-filler in C | ∃hasChild.Doctor |
| Universal | ∀R.C | All R-fillers in C | ∀hasChild.Vaccinated |
| Subsumption | C ⊑ D | All C are D | Apple ⊑ Fruit |

**DL Concepts vs Roles:**
- **Concepts** are like unary predicates (sets of individuals)
- **Roles** are like binary predicates (relationships between individuals)
- ∀hasSibling.Rich ✅ — concept (value restriction)
- Teens ⊓ Happy ✅ — concept (conjunction)
- ¬Doctor ✅ — concept (negation)
- hasBrother + hasFriend ❌ — NOT a concept (role expression)
- hasChild + hasChild ⊑ hasGrandchild ❌ — NOT a concept formula

**NNF (Negation Normal Form) in DL:**
- Push negation inward using:
  - ¬(C ⊓ D) = ¬C ⊔ ¬D
  - ¬(C ⊔ D) = ¬C ⊓ ¬D
  - ¬∀R.C = ∃R.¬C
  - ¬∃R.C = ∀R.¬C
  - ¬¬C = C

**DL Representation Patterns:**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **DL representation rules:**
> - **"All A are B"** → A ⊑ B (subsumption)
> - **"Some A are B"** → A ⊓ B ⊑ ⊤ (equivalent to "A ⊓ B is non-empty")
> - **"No A are B"** → A ⊓ B ⊑ ⊥ (A and B don't overlap)
> - **"People whose all children are vaccinated are proactive"** → (People ⊓ ∀hasChild.Vaccinated) ⊑ Proactive

**ALC Tableaux:**
- Reasoning method for checking satisfiability in ALC
- Similar to propositional tableaux but with quantifier-like rules
- Can determine: concept satisfiability, subsumption, instance checking

