## MASTER CHEAT SHEET — LAST MINUTE REVISION

### 1. FOL Quantifier Patterns (MOST TESTED!)

| English Statement | FOL Representation | Connector Used |
|---|---|---|
| All X are Y | ∀x (X(x) ⊃ Y(x)) | IMPLICATION |
| Some X are Y | ∃x (X(x) ∧ Y(x)) | CONJUNCTION |
| No X are Y | ∀x (X(x) ⊃ ¬Y(x)) | IMPLICATION + NEG |
| Only X are Y | ∀x (Y(x) ⊃ X(x)) | REVERSED IMPLICATION |
| Not all X are Y | ∃x (X(x) ∧ ¬Y(x)) | ∃ + CONJUNCTION |

> [!CAUTION]
> **"All" uses IMPLICATION (⊃), "Some" uses CONJUNCTION (∧)** — The #1 most common mistake on the exam!

